5. Who We Share Information With
We may provide your information to third party companies to perform certain services,
                            including but not limited to hosting services, payment processing, analytics and to assist
                            us in our marketing efforts. Where we share your information with third-party service
                            providers and business partners, we ensure that we have appropriate agreements in place to
                            protect your information as required by applicable data protection laws.
We may share information we collect or derive with third parties for the following purposes:
With service providers that perform services on our behalf, including the ones
                                referenced
                                above under “Third Party Services”;
With our affiliates;
For analytics and research purposes;
To satisfy any applicable laws, regulations or legal requirement;
To protect our or a third party’s legal rights or to defend against a legal claim;
As part of a business transfer such as a merger, acquisition, or at bankruptcy;
We may share aggregate or anonymous information about you with advertisers,
                                publishers,
                                business partners, sponsors, and other third parties; and
We may use analytics services provided by third parties, including Facebook, Apple,
                                Google
                                Analytics and Amazon.
6. How Long Do We Keep Your Information
We will retain your personal data only for as long as necessary in relation to the reason
                            that we hold it. The criteria used to determine our data retention periods include: (a) the
                            length of time we have an ongoing relationship with you; (b) whether there is a legal
                            obligation to which we are subject; and (c) whether retention is advisable in light of our
                            legal position (such as in regard to applicable statutes of limitations, litigation or
                            regulatory investigations).
7. Children
Our Services are not intended to be used by children under the age of 18.
8. The EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
The EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is a European Union regulation (2016/679).
                            It came into force on the 25th of May 2018. The aim of GDPR is to protect and enhance all EU
                            citizens’ data privacy rights. GDPR applies to anyone that holds or processes the data of an
                            EU citizen, regardless of where the person/company processing that data is based.
                            Information on the lawful basis for processing your personal data under the GDPR is set out
                            below.
Purpose of Processing
