9. Your Rights If You Are Located the EU
If You Are Located in the EU:
The GDPR provides certain rights to individuals including:
The right to receive detailed information on the processing of your personal data;
The right of access to personal data;
The right to rectify or erase personal data (known as the “right to be forgotten”);
The right to restrict processing;
The right of data portability;
The right to object to processing based on legitimate interests); and
The right to object to automated decision making, including profiling.
These rights may be subject to certain exemptions and may be restricted in certain
                            circumstances and pursuant to the law in your jurisdiction.
If you have any questions on how we process your data or wish to exercise any of your rights
                            please contact
info@kiragames.com
. We would hope
                            that we may resolve any issue that you
                            might have, however you also always have the right to lodge a complaint with the relevant
                            data protection supervisory authority in your jurisdiction if you are located in the EU.
If You Are Located in California:
Under the CCPA, you have the right to request a copy of your data, request we send your data
                            to a third party or that we delete your data. All of these rights are subject to
                            limitations.
Based on the CCPA’s broad definition of the term “sale,” certain data collection on our
                            Services by third parties for purposes of interest-based advertising and social media tools
                            may be a “sale” under the CCPA. You have the right to request that we do not sell your
                            information.
If you have any questions on how we process your data or wish to exercise any of your rights
                            please contact:
info@kiragames.com
.
10. Changes to our Privacy Policy
We may amend this Privacy Policy at any time in response to changing legal, technical or
                            business developments. If we make a change to how we collect, use, or share your personal
                            information, we will describe the changes, and, if required by law, seek your consent for
                            such changes. When we update our Privacy Policy, we will take appropriate measures to inform
                            you, consistent with the significance of the changes we make. Therefore, please review this
                            Privacy Policy from time to time so that you are aware when any changes are made to it.
11. Legal disclaimer
This Privacy Policy only covers the way we treat personal information and non-personal
                            information we collect on the Services. You should be aware that our website may from time
                            to time contain links to third-party websites.
Kiragames is not responsible for
